  "text_preview": "\"suggest\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► SUGGEST: The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"suggest / recommend / offer / propose\" The sign for \"suggest\" moves the palm-up flat hands in an arc forward and up and then down a bit. Think of \"laying an offer on the table.\" SUGGEST / OFFER / RECOMMEND: One handed version can mean PROPOSE / SUBMIT / ASSERT / BID: Sample sentence: If the class has a party, what would you suggest to do? Notes: See: SUBMIT See: PLAN See: REFER See: PROMISE * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy something from Dr. Bill's \" Bookstore .\" * Want even more ASL resources? Visit the \" ASL Training Center ! \" (Subscription Extension of ASLU) * Also check "
}
